BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:da368207-73a5-5697-8ecf-e6261032d532
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
SUMMARY:Meta-Layer Design Challenge
DESCRIPTION:The Meta-Layer Design Challenge is a global\, week-long design challenge
  exploring how learning\, collaboration\, and collective intelligence ca
 n be supported above the existing Web through a shared civic interface l
 ayer - the Meta-Layer. Rather than building new platforms\, participants
  are invited to design concepts\, interfaces\, and governance models tha
 t operate across websites using overlays\, shared context\, trust signal
 s\, and community coordination. The challenge emphasizes human-centered 
 design\, interoperability\, and public-interest outcomes. The Design Cha
 llenge is part of Meta-Layer Week (January 21–28\, 2025)\, co-hosted wit
 h Learning Planet. Activities include live sessions\, workshops\, demons
 trations\, office hours\, and a final showcase. Participants may submit 
 conceptual designs\, mockups\, diagrams\, governance proposals\, or ligh
 tweight prototypes. No coding is required. Both a Student Track and an O
 pen Track are offered\, with shared judging criteria focused on creativi
 ty\, feasibility\, and relevance to collective learning and public-inter
 est infrastructure. The challenge is relevant to Internet governance\, d
 igital public infrastructure\, education\, and community-driven innovati
 on\, and aligns with long-standing Internet Society interests in an open
 \, trustworthy\, and people-centered Internet.  Audience: Students\, edu
 cators\, designers\, technologists\, researchers\, and community organiz
 ers
URL:https://luma.com/lpml
DTSTART;TZID=PST:20260121T113000
DTEND;TZID=PST:20260128T130000
END:VEVENT
